Whereof saith Haymo: As the philosophers said, and doctors have opinion, this air is also full of devils and of wicked spirits as the sunbeams be full of small motes, which is small dust or powder. And if any of them be overcome of any holy man, he may never after tempt a man of that vice of which he is overcome.
